An argument decorated with [CallerFilePath] in a default constructor that is called implicitly by a derived class is left at its default value (not set to the file path). It works if that constructor is called explicitly via `: base()`.

**Version Used**:

.NET SDK (reflecting any global.json):
 Version:   5.0.200-preview.21079.7
 Commit:    580b1c3770

Microsoft (R) Visual C# Compiler version 3.9.0-4.21104.8 (2fc92d84)

**Steps to Reproduce**:

Run the following program as a console EXE:

```
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            new DerivedClass();
        }
    }

    class BaseClass
    {
        //[MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.NoInlining | MethodImplOptions.NoOptimization)] // doesn't help
        public BaseClass([CallerFilePath] string callerFilePath = "[not provided]")
        {
            System.Console.WriteLine("BaseClass callerFilePath = " + callerFilePath);
        }
    }

    class DerivedClass : BaseClass
    {
        public DerivedClass([CallerFilePath] string callerFilePath = "[not provided]")
            // works if you uncomment this:
            // : base()
        {
            System.Console.WriteLine("DerivedClass callerFilePath = " + callerFilePath);
        }
    }
```

**Expected Behavior**:

> BaseClass callerFilePath = ...\CallerFilePathTest\Program.cs
> DerivedClass callerFilePath = ...\CallerFilePathTest\Program.cs

**Actual Behavior**:

> BaseClass callerFilePath = [not provided]
> DerivedClass callerFilePath = ...\CallerFilePathTest\Program.cs

**Version Used**: 

**Steps to Reproduce**:

1. Create a new .NET 5 class library
2. Replace `Program.cs` with this code:

```c#
using System;
using System.Text.RegularExpressions;

namespace ClassLibrary39
{
    record R(Regex Regex, Uri uri);

    public class Class1
    {
    }
}
```

3. Invoke _Move type to R.cs_ on the record.

**Expected Behavior**:

Record is created with using directives so that `Regex` and `Uri` are resolved.

```c#
// R.cs
using System;
using System.Text.RegularExpressions;
namespace ClassLibrary39
{
    internal sealed record R(Regex Regex, Uri uri);
}
```

**Actual Behavior**:

Type is moved to file without usings, so symbols are unresolved and code does not compile.

```c#
// R.cs
namespace ClassLibrary39
{
    internal sealed record R(Regex Regex, Uri uri);
}
```

